iff#comment-39476610"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "Minor comment and it should be good to go.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Minor comment and it should be good to go.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-23T18:13:52.269463+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andr\u00e9s Fortier", "uuid": "{f9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3/4af4377f-d065-496d-8cd4-01d5c760c6a3/128"}}, "nickname": "andres_fortier", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3"}, "updated_on": "2017-06-23T18:13:52.272337+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39476610}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39476593.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39476593"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "Instead of \"The event is prevented\" I would say that you are stopping the event propagation, hence making the default action (which is to select the row) not to happen.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Instead of \"The event is prevented\" I would say that you are stopping the event propagation, hence making the default action (which is to select the row) not to happen.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-23T18:13:36.199641+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andr\u00e9s Fortier", "uuid": "{f9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3/4af4377f-d065-496d-8cd4-01d5c760c6a3/128"}}, "nickname": "andres_fortier", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-23T18:13:36.202429+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39476593}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39474603.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39474603"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "I addressed the comment @andres_fortier . preventing the event works great. That way we not only avoid having the setTimeout, but also we don't need to assign an ID to the Data Table, to clear it's selection.\n\nptal again @andres_fortier \n\nI managed to capture some GIFs of the issue, before and after:\n\nBefore. Notice how some clicks don't open the menu (because the row was being deselected)\n\n![before2selection.gif](https://bitbucket.org/repo/oyRq5d/images/3808610175-before2selection.gif 'before2selection.gif')\n\nAfter.\n\n![after2selection.gif](https://bitbucket.org/repo/oyRq5d/images/340541061-after2selection.gif 'after2selection.gif')", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I addressed the comment @andres_fortier . preventing the event works great. That way we not only avoid having the setTimeout, but also we don't need to assign an ID to the Data Table, to clear it's selection.</p>\n<p>ptal again @andres_fortier </p>\n<p>I managed to capture some GIFs of the issue, before and after:</p>\n<p>Before. Notice how some clicks don't open the menu (because the row was being deselected)</p>\n<p><img alt=\"before2selection.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/oyRq5d/images/3808610175-before2selection.gif\" title=\"before2selection.gif\" /></p>\n<p>After.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"after2selection.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/oyRq5d/images/340541061-after2selection.gif\" title=\"after2selection.gif\" /></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-23T17:38:38.150789+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "uuid": "{4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384/b758f5b1-8d6c-4aa7-8106-ebf2b29bc9a9/128"}}, "nickname": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384"}, "updated_on": "2017-06-23T17:38:38.158255+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39474603}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"update": {"description": "In this PR I address [CLOUD-164](https://osrfoundation.atlassian.net/browse/CLOUD-164).\r\n\r\nThe Iron Data Table element, whenever a row is clicked, fires a \"selecting item\" event. When this happens, we open the configuration dialog.\r\n\r\nA click on a row toggles the selection, so the event doesn't fires when it's being deselected. As no visual feedback is provided for the selection, this might be misleading: The row is clicked but the dialog doesn't shows up.\r\n\r\nAs no other event lets us change this behavior, we can prevent this by clearing the selection of the row every time one is selected. This causes clicks to always fire the data table's `on-selecting-item` event.\r\n\r\nWith the callback of this event, we need to call a `setTimeout`, to let the dialog render as desired. \r\n\r\nptal @andres_fortier \r\n\r\n**Note:** I couldn't find a way to represent mouse click events visually, so a screenshot or animation would be ambiguous. I'd advice to update to this branch and test this change.\r\n\r\nNotice that the change is repeated through Keys, Machine Types and User Metrics elements.", "title": "Data table click", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "5c3df851b203", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commit/5c3df851b203.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commits/5c3df851b203"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-widgets", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-widgets", "uuid": "{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "f795d6846bd7", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commit/f795d6846bd7.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commits/f795d6846bd7"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-widgets", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-widgets", "uuid": "{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}"}, "branch": {"name": "data-table-click"}}, "state": "OPEN", "author": {"display_name": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "uuid": "{4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384/b758f5b1-8d6c-4aa7-8106-ebf2b29bc9a9/128"}}, "nickname": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384"}, "date": "2017-06-23T17:27:27.047483+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39460949.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39460949"}}, "parent": {"id": 39458726, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39458726.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff