f": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "I agree. Do you think this should be addressed as a separated task? I assume that the elements having these names include not only Machine Type but also Keys and User Metrics (although we have been renaming many in the last one)\n\nAbout the dialog, I think the \"on\" can be replaced with \"open\". Perhaps open Edit Dialog or Options Dialog.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I agree. Do you think this should be addressed as a separated task? I assume that the elements having these names include not only Machine Type but also Keys and User Metrics (although we have been renaming many in the last one)</p>\n<p>About the dialog, I think the \"on\" can be replaced with \"open\". Perhaps open Edit Dialog or Options Dialog.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-23T13:59:21.322184+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "uuid": "{4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384/b758f5b1-8d6c-4aa7-8106-ebf2b29bc9a9/128"}}, "nickname": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-23T13:59:21.325619+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39458726}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39458301.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39458301"}}, "parent": {"id": 39403006, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39403006.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39403006"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "I thought the same, but if it's outside the timeout, the clear selection is not happening as expected. I'll take a closer look to these events.\n\nThanks for the link!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I thought the same, but if it's outside the timeout, the clear selection is not happening as expected. I'll take a closer look to these events.</p>\n<p>Thanks for the link!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-23T13:55:03.984600+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "uuid": "{4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384/b758f5b1-8d6c-4aa7-8106-ebf2b29bc9a9/128"}}, "nickname": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ebe9f39d-0ca2-4f29-82cf-6cc3df017384"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-23T13:55:03.987098+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39458301}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39409823.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39409823"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "While I know this is not strictly part of this PR, we should consider using descriptive names when possible. So e.g. we have things like:\n\n```      \n      on-created=\"_onMachineTypeCreated\"\n      on-deleted=\"_onMachineTypeDeleted\"\n      on-updated=\"_onMachineTypeUpdated\"\n```\n\nbut then we have `on-selecting-item=\"_onMachineTypeDialog\"` which is not clear on what it does. I would suggest either naming the handler based on the event (e.g. `_onMachineTypeSelected`) or on the expected action (e.g. `_onMachineTypeDialogOpen` -although the \"on\" in this case feels weird-).", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>While I know this is not strictly part of this PR, we should consider using descriptive names when possible. So e.g. we have things like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>      on-created=&quot;_onMachineTypeCreated&quot;\n      on-deleted=&quot;_onMachineTypeDeleted&quot;\n      on-updated=&quot;_onMachineTypeUpdated&quot;\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>but then we have <code>on-selecting-item=\"_onMachineTypeDialog\"</code> which is not clear on what it does. I would suggest either naming the handler based on the event (e.g. <code>_onMachineTypeSelected</code>) or on the expected action (e.g. <code>_onMachineTypeDialogOpen</code> -although the \"on\" in this case feels weird-).</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-22T22:00:39.924967+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andr\u00e9s Fortier", "uuid": "{f9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3/4af4377f-d065-496d-8cd4-01d5c760c6a3/128"}}, "nickname": "andres_fortier", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-22T22:00:39.927339+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39409823}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39409567.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39409567"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "So, this gets repeated three times. Can't we create a common helper function or extend the dialog component so this can be factored out?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>So, this gets repeated three times. Can't we create a common helper function or extend the dialog component so this can be factored out?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-22T21:54:52.620200+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andr\u00e9s Fortier", "uuid": "{f9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3/4af4377f-d065-496d-8cd4-01d5c760c6a3/128"}}, "nickname": "andres_fortier", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-22T21:54:52.622457+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39409567}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208/comments/39403006.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208/_/diff#comment-39403006"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}, "content": {"raw": "is the `clearSelection()` needed inside the timeout? I thought that something like the following should work:\n\n```\ns3keyDataTable.clearSelection()\nsetTimeout(function(s3keyDialog) {\n    s3keyDialog.open()\n}, 0, this.$.s3keyDialog)\n```\n\nAlso, can you be more descriptive about why the timeout is needed (there is a great explanation in https://stackoverflow.com/questions/779379/why-is-settimeoutfn-0-sometimes-useful, check the second answer)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>is the <code>clearSelection()</code> needed inside the timeout? I thought that something like the following should work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>s3keyDataTable.clearSelection()\nsetTimeout(function(s3keyDialog) {\n    s3keyDialog.open()\n}, 0, this.$.s3keyDialog)\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Also, can you be more descriptive about why the timeout is needed (there is a great explanation in <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/779379/why-is-settimeoutfn-0-sometimes-useful\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/779379/why-is-settimeoutfn-0-sometimes-useful</a>, check the second answer)</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-22T19:57:25.750291+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andr\u00e9s Fortier", "uuid": "{f9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf9c4496c-9146-4675-b1d5-bd0ed156cf58%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3/4af4377f-d065-496d-8cd4-01d5c760c6a3/128"}}, "nickname": "andres_fortier", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c59901bb-7eb0-4d2c-966f-7c66c154fef3"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-06-22T20:01:17.426215+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 39403006}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 208, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pullrequests/208.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/pull-requests/208"}}, "title": "Data table click"}}, {"update": {"description": "In this PR I address [CLOUD-164](https://osrfoundation.atlassian.net/browse/CLOUD-164).\r\n\r\nThe Iron Data Table element, whenever a row is clicked, fires a \"selecting item\" event. When this happens, we open the configuration dialog.\r\n\r\nA click on a row toggles the selection, so the event doesn't fires when it's being deselected. As no visual feedback is provided for the selection, this might be misleading: The row is clicked but the dialog doesn't shows up.\r\n\r\nAs no other event lets us change this behavior, we can prevent this by clearing the selection of the row every time one is selected. This causes clicks to always fire the data table's `on-selecting-item` event.\r\n\r\nWith the callback of this event, we need to call a `setTimeout`, to let the dialog render as desired. \r\n\r\nptal @andres_fortier \r\n\r\n**Note:** I couldn't find a way to represent mouse click events visually, so a screenshot or animation would be ambiguous. I'd advice to update to this branch and test this change.\r\n\r\nNotice that the change is repeated through Keys, Machine Types and User Metrics elements.", "title": "Data table click", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "0c8f2770617e", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commit/0c8f2770617e.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commits/0c8f2770617e"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-widgets", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-widgets", "uuid": "{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "0d08bfef68e5", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commit/0d08bfef68e5.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets/commits/0d08bfef68e5"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-widgets.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-widgets"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-widgets", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-widgets", "uuid": "{99f16044-e8c9-4af0-bb6e-51477582665b}"}, "branch": {"name": "data-table-click"}}, "state": "OPEN", "author": {"display_name": "Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1s", "uuid": "{4135c724-adb3-4ffb-a983-57bf615c4d1c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B4135c724-adb3-4f